新冠肺炎｜值得严重关注的2019年12月31日	。
NEW GUINEA Pneumonia deserves serious attention on December 31, 2019.
陈晓雪  ·   2020/02/19	。
Chen Xiaoxue 2020 / 02 / 19.
- 编者按 -回顾新冠肺炎疫情，可以看到一个关键日期，2019年12月31日。
- Editor's press - Review of the New Crown Pneumonia outbreak, you can see a key date, December 31, 2019.
这一天，国家卫健委专家组在武汉开会，香港提出对疫情的关注。
On this day, the national health committee expert group meeting in Wuhan, Hong Kong raised concerns about the epidemic.
如果这天会议确定要采取行动，包括不宣传但行动的外松内紧，而不是掉以轻心，可能对于疫情发展会有很大影响。
If the day's meeting identifies actions to be taken, including non-advocacy but loose internal constraints to action, rather than complacency, it could have a significant impact on the course of the epidemic.
那么，12月31日，我们有机会吗？本文试图总结经验，看我们在体制上可以有何改革、在做事方式上有何根本性的改变。
So, do we have a chance on December 31This article attempts to take stock of what changes we can make institutionally and fundamentally change the way we do things.
疾病控制这样的大事，处理方式应该更接近救火队，而不应该接近法庭判死刑的过程，后者可以有时间，前者需要快速，疑病从有。
Events such as disease control should be handled more closely to fire brigades than to the process of sentencing to death by the courts, which can have time, the former requiring speed and suspected illness.
本文试图提出三个疑问：1. 中国疾控中心的网络直报系统或传染病信息系统，有没有发挥作用？究竟何时发挥作用？为何多个信源呈现出来的信息是矛盾的？2. 2019年12月31日，武汉已经对病人采取隔离措施，但为何未要求医护人员采取防护措施？即使是外松内紧，内紧体现在哪里？3.2019年12月31日，为何香港已经开始提醒公众防护，为何武汉却没有提醒公众防护？下面这张图，回顾了截至2月11日国内新冠肺炎的全部病例。
This paper tries to ask three questions: 1. Has China CDC's network direct reporting system or infectious disease information system worked? When did it work? Why did Wuhan require medical staff to take protective measures even if it was internally tight? 3.12.2019 Why was Wuhan not alerting the public to the need for protection?
如果在2019年12月31日，武汉能够有强有力的措施阻止传播，新冠肺炎可能被扑灭，而不是今天的大流行。
If Wuhan had strong measures in place by December 31, 2019 to stop the spread of the disease, it might be able to put out the pneumonia, rather than the current pandemic.
图源：中华流行病学杂志，2020.撰文 | 陈晓雪责编 | 李晓明● 　● 　●01回到2019年12月30日2019年12月31日，根据武汉当地媒体的报道，20万武汉市民和游客参加了跨年的长江灯光秀。
Source: China Epidemiology Journal, 2020.Writing & # 44; Chen Xiaoxue at & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp;
当日的媒体上并没有提及的是：这一天，世卫组织驻华代表处获悉在中国湖北省武汉市发现不明原因肺炎病例。
What was not mentioned in the media on that day was that the WHO representative office in China was informed of the discovery of an unidentified pneumonia case in Wuhan, Hubei Province, China.
这一天，国家卫健委第一批专家组抵达武汉，调查武汉的不明肺炎。
On that day, the first group of experts from the National Health Commission arrived in Wuhan to investigate unidentified pneumonia.
对于国家卫健委第一批专家组来汉，据经济学家华生2月16日的文章，中国疾控中心主任高福看到网络上流传的不明肺炎信息，从而起到了重要推动作用。
Gao Fu, director of the China CDC, played an important role in promoting the discovery of unidentified pneumonia information circulating on the Internet, according to an article by the economist Watson Feb. 16.
然而，据《知识分子》2月17日获得的一份流出的报告显示，湖北省疾控中心和武汉市疾控中心以及几个区级的疾控中心早在2019年12月29日就调查武汉市不明肺炎的情况，并形成了报告。
However, according to an outflow report obtained by the Intellectuals on Feb. 17, the CDC in Hubei Province and Wuhan City, as well as several district-level CDC, investigated and reported unidentified pneumonia in Wuhan as early as December 29, 2019.
那么，两个不同来源的信息让人不免疑惑：中国疾控中心是否收到了这份报告？国家卫健委第一批专家组对武汉当地的疫情应对给出了怎样的指导意见？回到2019年12月30日。
So, two different sources of information leave no doubt: Did the CDC receive the report? What did the first group of health experts say about the response to the local epidemic in Wuhan? Back to December 30, 2019.
这一天，一个叫李文亮的眼科医生在班级群里提醒同学—— “确诊了7例SARS”。
One day, an ophthalmologist named Li Wenliang reminded his classmates in the class that "seven cases of SARS were diagnosed."
同样在这一天，经济学家华生上述的文章披露：“去年12月30日……由于高福有在睡前在网络上搜索有关传染病信息的习惯，偶然发现了有关武汉市卫健委内部发出了不明原因肺炎紧急通知的相关传闻，这让他大吃一惊。
Also on the same day, the economist Watson said: "He was surprised to find rumors that an emergency notice of pneumonia had been issued within the Wuhan Health Care Commission because of Gao Fu's habit of searching the Internet for information about infectious diseases before going to bed.
”“因为他去年还在政协会上拍着胸脯说，现在有了这个疾病直报系统，象SARS那样的大疫情不会再发生。
"Because he patted his chest at the CPPCC meeting last year, there is now a direct reporting system and a pandemic like SARS will not happen again.
所以他随即打电话给武汉市疾控中心负责人了解情况，在得到肯定的答复之后，立即问他们案例早已超过三例必报的预警门槛，为什么这么多天来从未向网络系统直报？都这样的话，国家重金打造的网络直报系统还有什么用？”华生说，据知情人透露，从对方含糊的解释中，高福感到问题不小，自己责任重大，连夜给国家卫健委多名领导分别打电话报警。
So he called the head of Wuhan CDC to find out what the situation was like, and immediately after receiving a positive response, he asked them why there had been more than three reported cases and why he had never reported directly to a network system for so many days.
“据媒体报道，国家卫健委也可算行动迅速，第二天就由分管领导带领工作组、专家组到达武汉。
"According to media reports, the National Health Commission can also count on rapid action, the next day led by the lead team, the team of experts to Wuhan.
”华生认为，据这个消息，高福实际上是12月30号武汉几名医生在朋友圈发消息提醒的同一天晚上， “体制内最高级别的报警人”。
According to Watson, Gao Fu was actually the "highest-ranking police officer in the system" on December 30, the same night several Wuhan doctors alerted friends.
就在这一天，湖北省已经有一份不明肺炎疫情的流调报告出炉。
On that day, a report of an outbreak of unknown pneumonia was issued in Hubei province.
但直到2月17日，报告流出。
However, no outflows were reported until 17 February.
这份报告显示，湖北省、市、区疾控中心联合调查组在2019年12月29日已就华南海鲜市场多例肺炎病例情况进行调查，并在12月30日形成了报告。
The report showed that on December 29, 2019, the joint investigation team of Hubei province, city and district CDC had investigated a number of cases of pneumonia in the south China seafood market, and a report was issued on December 30.
“2019年12月29日下午，接省、市卫健委通知，近期省中西医结合医院、市中心医院后湖区等医院收治多例症状相似的肺炎病例，有华南海鲜市场暴露史”，报告披露，湖北省疾控中心、武汉市疾控中心会同江汉、硚口、东西湖区疾控中心赴现场开展流行病学调查、标本采集检测、院感控制等处置工作。
"On the afternoon of December 29, 2019, the provincial and municipal health committee informed that the provincial Chinese and Western medicine combined hospitals, post-lake area hospitals and other hospitals recently admitted many similar cases of pneumonia, with exposure history of the South China seafood market.
根据《中国新闻周刊》的报道，2019年12月28日，武汉市中心医院后湖院区急诊科接诊了4例和华南海鲜市场有关的发热病人。
According to China News Weekly, on December 28, 2019, four cases of febrile patients related to the South China seafood market were admitted to the emergency department of the Houhu courtyard of Wuhan Central Hospital.
到2020年1月1日前后，医院共收治了7例“不明原因肺炎”病例。
Up to and around January 1, 2020, seven cases of "unspecified pneumonia" have been admitted to hospitals.
2019年12月29日，武汉市中心医院急诊科向医院公共卫生科上报了这7例发热病人中急诊科收治的4例。
On December 29, 2019, the emergency department of Wuhan Central Hospital reported 4 of the 7 febrile patients to the public health department of the hospital.
公共卫生科回复称，已上报江汉区疾控中心。
Public Health Section replied that reported to the JiangHan District CDC.
在急诊科上报的4例病例中，有一对母子，儿子在华南海鲜市场工作，母亲去海鲜市场送饭，并没有接触过华南海鲜市场的物品，但依然染病，而且病情较重。
Of the four cases reported by the emergency department, one mother and one son were working at the South China seafood market, while the mother went to the seafood market to deliver food and had no contact with the South China seafood market.
武汉市中心医院急诊科主任艾芬告诉《中国新闻周刊》，她当时就判断这个病可能 “人传人”。
Evan, director of emergency department at Wuhan Central Hospital, told China News Weekly that she had judged the disease to be "human-to-human."
与此同时，湖北省中西医结合医院也陆续收治了7名不明肺炎的病人，该院呼吸与重症医学科主任张继先医生和院方也将病人的情况在12月27日上报给了江汉区疾控中心，并在12月29日上报给省、市卫健委的疾控处。
Meanwhile, seven patients with unidentified pneumonia were admitted to the Hubei Provincial Chinese and Western Medical Association Hospital. Zhang Jixian, director of respiratory and severe medicine and the hospital's hospital, reported the patient's condition to the CDC on December 27 and to the CDC's disease control office on December 29.
2019年12月29日， “省卫健委疾控处和市卫健委疾控处快速反应，指示武汉市疾控中心、金银潭医院和江汉区疾控中心，来到医院，开始流行病学调查” （据《长江日报》2020年2月2日的报道）。
On December 29, 2019, the "Provincial Health Care and Disease Control Office and the Municipal Health and Wellness Control Office, instructed Wuhan CDC, Gold and Silver Pool Hospital and the Jianghan CDC to come to the hospital and start an epidemiological investigation," Changjiang Daily reported on February 2, 2020.
前述12月30日完成的不明肺炎流调报告称，累计搜索病例25例，完成流行病学调查核实20例，其中华南海鲜市场西区12个摊位、东区1个摊位，为17人，另外市场非固定摊位工作人员3人。
According to the aforementioned report on Unknown Pneumonia completed on December 30, 25 cases were accumulated and 20 cases were confirmed by epidemiological investigation, including 12 stalls in the Western and 1 in the Eastern District of the South China Seafood Market, and 3 non-fixed-pitch workers in the market.
报告介绍，有两个家庭成员有在该市场共同暴露，其中一个患者有4个家庭成员感染，一个患者家庭有2个家庭成员感染。
The report describes two family members who were exposed together at the market, one with four family members infected and one with two family members infected.
在时间分布上，调查病例的最早发病时间为12月12日，最后一例为12月25日。
In terms of time distribution, the earliest occurrence of the investigated cases was 12 December, and the last case was 25 December.
报告对于下一步处置的建议是：（一）市场监督部门加强该市场卫生环境综合整理，切实做好环境清洗消毒，日常通风等工作。
The recommendations of the report on the way forward are as follows: (1) The market supervisory department should strengthen the overall arrangement of the sanitary environment in the market, and effectively clean and disinfect the environment and provide daily ventilation.
（二）卫生健康部门进一步加强该市场从业相关人群的不明原因疾病的检测工作，做好对可疑患者的早发现、早排查、早处置工作。
(2) The health authorities shall further strengthen the work of detecting unknown causes of diseases among the relevant groups in the market, and make efforts for early detection, early detection and early treatment of suspicious patients.
（三）各医疗机构进一步规范发热门诊的运行和预诊分诊，早期明确诊断和规范治疗，做好感染控制工作。
(3) Medical institutions shall further standardize the operation of the fever clinic and the pre-diagnosis and consultation, clearly diagnose and standardize the treatment at an early stage, and do a good job in infection control.
02报告应汇报给谁？假设上述内部流出报告为真，那么应该汇报给哪些机构？在我国，国家、省市、区县都有各级的疾控中心，隶属于各级卫健委，而各级卫健委是各级政府的组成部门。
To whom should the report be reported? If the above-mentioned internal outflow report is true, which organizations should be reported to? In China, there are CDC at all levels in China, subordinate to all levels of health care committee, and all levels of health care committee is an integral part of all levels of government.
据21世纪经济报道，地方的疾控中心主要向当地的卫健委和政府汇报。
According to the 21st Century Economic Report, local Centers for Disease Control report mainly to local health authorities and the government.
也就是说，当这份报告形成后，武汉市卫健委、武汉市政府、湖北省卫健委和湖北省政府是汇报对象之一。
That is to say, when the report formed, Wuhan Wei Bodyguard Commission, Wuhan city government, Hubei Weijian committee and Hubei provincial government is one of the object of the report.
而根据中国疾控中心官网的《传染病信息报告管理规范》，各级疾病预防控制机构要及时将疫情分析结果以信息、简报或报告等形式向上级疾病预防控制机构和同级卫生计生行政部门报告，并反馈到下一级疾病预防控制机构。
According to the Regulations on Reporting and Management of Infectious Disease Information of the Official Network of the China CDC, disease prevention and control organizations at all levels should promptly report the results of epidemic situation analysis in the form of information, bulletins or reports to higher-level disease prevention and control agencies and health and family planning authorities at the same level.
也就是说，中国疾控中心也应该是汇报的对象之一。
In other words, China CDC should also be one of the reporting targets.
另根据《经济观察报》报道，中国疾控中心在2003年SARS疫情后，建立了一套综合的监测系统，最先建立起来的是传染病网络直报系统，横向覆盖全国，纵向可达乡镇医生卫生院。
According to the Economic Observer, China's CDC set up an integrated surveillance system after the SARS epidemic in 2003, starting with the Communicable Disease Network Direct Reporting System, with horizontal national coverage and vertical access to township doctors' clinics.
“只要发现传染性病例、尤其是不明原因肺炎，医院都要直接在这套系统上报告病例，包括中国疾控中心在内的各级疾控部门都能第一时间了解情况。
"Hospitals report cases directly on the system whenever cases of infectious disease, especially pneumonia, are discovered, and disease control authorities at all levels, including the China CDC, have immediate access to information.
”中国疾控中心原副主任杨功焕介绍说。
Yang Kun-hwan, former deputy director of the China CDC, said.
而据《第一财经》报道，这套系统也设置了针对不明原因肺炎PUE（Pneumonia of Unknown Etiology）的直报。
The system also features a direct report on Pneumonia of Unknown Diseases, according to First Finance.
如果在武汉发生了多例不明原因的肺炎，而且比较集中，杨功焕在接受《经济观察报》采访时表示，按照这个报告体系，中国疾控中心应该会收到相关的报告。
In an interview with the Economic Observer, Yang said the CDC should receive a report if there were a number of cases of unspecified pneumonia in Wuhan.
她认为，中国疾控中心即使没有人下去调查，也可以发现武汉出现的情况。
She said the CDC could find out what was happening in Wuhan, even if no one went down to investigate.
“按道理，这个机制下，在这个时候中国疾控中心可能会派人，地方省疾控或者市疾控也有权力派人下去做流行病学调查，确认病情，然后来报告。
"It makes sense that under this mechanism, the CDC might have personnel at that time, and local disease control or city disease control authorities would have the power to send people down for epidemiological investigation to confirm the disease and report back."
同时，医院在这种情况下也应该实施隔离的。
At the same time, hospitals should be segregated in such cases.
”但是，根据华生的文章，作为中国疾控中心主任，高福在2019年12月30日未收到湖北或武汉任何关于不明原因肺炎的报告，对湖北省、市、区三级疾控中心的这一报告显然也不知情。
However, according to Watson's article, Gao Fuk, the director of the China CDC, did not receive any report of unspecified pneumonia in Hubei or Wuhan on December 30, 2019, nor was he aware of the report from the CDC of Hubei province, city or district.
一位业内人士评论说，如果这份省、市、区疾控中心联合调查组形成的报告没有报送中国疾控中心，那就是体制的问题，需要改进，不能只报当地政府，而不报中国疾控中心；如果这份报告抄送了中国疾控中心，而中国疾控中心主任自己不知情，那就是中国疾控中心的问题。
'If the report from the CDC joint investigation team isn't sent to the CDC, it's a systemic problem that needs to be improved, 'said one industry source.' If the report is copied to the CDC and the CDC director doesn't know it, it's a systemic problem that needs to be improved.
032019年12月31日这一天，国家卫健委专家组抵达武汉。
032019 On 31 December 2019, the team of experts from the National Health Commission arrived in Wuhan.
直到今天，我们仍无法从官方渠道获悉这批专家去了哪里、对于武汉的疫情给出了怎样的疫情应对办法，以及处置工作的指导意见的详情，只能根据媒体的零星报道或一些新闻稿去还原当时的情况。
To this day, we are still unable to learn from official sources where the experts went, how to deal with the epidemic in Wuhan, and the details of the handling of the epidemic, but only on the basis of sporadic media reports or some press releases.
据《中国新闻周刊》报道，第一批国家卫健委专家组成员有北京地坛医院感染性疾病诊疗与研究中心首席专家李兴旺、中日友好医院呼吸与危重症医学科主任曹彬，还有中国疾控中心传染病预防控制国家重点实验室主任徐建国。
According to China News Weekly, the first batch of national health committee experts included Li Changsheng, chief expert of the Center for Diagnosis and Research of Infectious Diseases at Ditan Hospital in Beijing, Cao Bin, director of respiratory and critical medicine at the Sino-Japanese Friendship Hospital, and Xu Jianguo, director of the National Key Laboratory for Infectious Disease Prevention and Control at the China CDC.
据中国疾控中心官网转载的新华社的报道，2019年12月31日，根据中国疾控中心要求，病毒病所（即中国疾病预防控制中心病毒病预防控制所）选派专家组赴武汉参加疫情防控。
On December 31, 2019, at the request of China's CDC, the China Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) sent a team of experts to Wuhan to participate in disease prevention and control, Xinhua reported.
于2020年1月1日上午赴华南海鲜市场，针对病例相关商户及相关街区集中采集环境样本515份，运送至中国疾控中心病毒病所进行检测；1月12日，病毒病所专家再次在华南海鲜市场采集野生动物贩卖商铺相关标本70份，并转运至实验室进行检测。
On the morning of January 1, 2020, 515 environmental samples were collected and sent to the China Centers for Disease Control and Prevention for testing at the South China Seafood Market. On January 12, experts from the Institute of Virus Disease again collected 70 specimens from wildlife shops in the South China Seafood Market and transferred them to laboratories for testing.
据财新的报道，第一批专家到武汉金银潭医院做过调查，并做了一套“不明原因的病毒性肺炎”的诊断标准，要有华南海鲜市场接触史，要有发烧症状，要做全基因组测序，这三条标准都达到了，才能确诊。
According to Caixin report, the first batch of experts to Wuhan gold and silver pool hospital to do an investigation, and made a set of "unknown causes of viral pneumonia" diagnosis criteria, to have a history of exposure to the South China seafood market, to have fever symptoms, to do a whole genome sequencing, these three criteria have been met.
据《大公报》报道，中国疾病预防控制中心传染病预防控制所所长徐建国1月4日表示，从目前看，未发现明显的人传人证据，未发现医务人员感染，且没有发生死亡案例，说明病毒威胁水平有限。
Xu Jianguo, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Infectious Disease Prevention and Control Institute, said on Thursday that he had found no evidence of human-to-human transmission, no cases of infection among medical personnel and no deaths.
徐建国还强调，中国的传染病控制有多年的积累，绝不会出现因为春运发生大扩散的可能性。
Xu also stressed that China's infectious disease control has accumulated over the years, there will never be a great spread because of the possibility of spring transportation.
2019年12月31日，在国家卫健委专家组到达武汉的当天，武汉市卫健委发布了第一份关于肺炎疫情的通告，表示到目前为止调查发现27例病例，其中7例病情严重，并称所有病例已隔离治疗，密切接触者的追踪调查和医学观察正在进行中，“到目前为止调查未发现明显人传人现象，未发现医务人员感染”，对病原的检测及感染原因的调查正在进行中。
On December 31, 2019, on the day the team arrived in Wuhan, Wuhan's health committee issued its first notice of pneumonia, saying that investigations had found 27 cases so far, seven of them serious, that all cases had been isolated, that close contacts were being followed up and that medical observation was under way.
通告还透露，武汉同济医院、省疾控中心、中科院武汉病毒所、武汉市传染病医院及武汉市疾控中心等单位等临床医学、流行病学、病毒学专家进行了会诊，专家从病情、治疗转归、流行病学调查、实验室初步检测等方面情况分析认为上述病例系病毒性肺炎。
Wuhan Tongji Hospital, Provincial CDC, Wuhan Hospital of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, Wuhan Infectious Diseases Hospital and Wuhan CDC were consulted by clinical medicine, epidemiology and virology specialists, who identified the cases as viral pneumonia from the aspects of illness, outcome of treatment, epidemiological investigation and preliminary laboratory tests.
而武汉市卫健委发布的第二份关于疫情的通告，也就是在2020年1月3日，首次提出了“不明原因的病毒性肺炎”的概念，表示符合不明原因的病毒性肺炎诊断患者有44例，其中重症11例，均在武汉市医疗机构接受隔离治疗。
On January 3, 2020, the concept of "unspecified viral pneumonia" was introduced for the first time, indicating that 44 patients with unspecified viral pneumonia were diagnosed, 11 of whom were treated in isolation in Wuhan medical institutions.
这份通告也提到，国家和省卫生健康委派出工作组和专家组赴武汉市，指导当地开展疫情应对和处置工作。
The circular also mentioned that national and provincial health teams and teams of experts were sent to Wuhan city to guide the local epidemic response and disposal efforts.
“初步调查表明，未发现明显的人传人证据，未发现医务人员感染。
"Preliminary investigations have shown no clear evidence of human-to-human transmission and no infection by medical personnel.
”这份公告，中国疾控中心进行了全文转载。
The announcement was reproduced in full by the China CDC.
据《三联生活周刊》报道，武汉的一位医生将武汉卫生系统初期对新冠肺炎的举措解读为 “内紧外松”：“紧” 是及时发现病例，并做了严格的隔离和应对；“松” 则是没有大范围地公告社会，让大家对疾病提起警惕，也没有号召大家戴口罩。
According to Triple Life Weekly, a doctor in Wuhan interpreted Wuhan's initial response to the new crown pneumonia as "tight": "tight" is the timely detection of cases and strict isolation and response; "loose" is not a large-scale announcement of the community to alert people to disease, and did not call for people to wear masks.
内紧外松，也可以用来解读中国疾控中心应对疫情的策略。
External tight, can also be used to understand China's CDC response to the epidemic strategy.
冯子健在接受《新京报》采访时表示，中国疾控中心从最早开始，就把新冠肺炎当作有高度传染性的疾病来对待，第一时间采取了密切接触者管理等措施，但公布信息是“谨慎的”，从开始的“未发现明显人传人现象”到“不能排除有限人传人的可能”，需要一个过程，因为对疾病的认识有个过程，和病例诊断、实验室检测结果逐步用于病人的甄别有关。
In an interview with the Beijing News, Feng Zi-jian said the CDC had treated the new crown pneumonia as a highly contagious disease since its earliest days. It had first taken measures such as close contact management, but the release of information was "prudent" from the beginning of "no apparent human-to-human transmission" to "limited human-to-human potential."
然而，根据疫情上报第一人、被记大功的张继先和其他医生接受媒体采访的内容，尽管武汉市卫健委表示对病人进行隔离治疗，但对一线的医护人员似乎并没有给出提高防护等级的建议。
However, Zhang Jixian and other doctors who reported the outbreak to the first person, Zhang Jixian and other doctors were interviewed by the media. Although the Wuhan municipal health committee said patients should be treated in isolation, front-line medical personnel do not appear to have given recommendations for raising the level of protection.
在《长江日报》的报道中，张继先在2019年12月27日和29日连续报告不明肺炎的情况后，医院给她的科室批了N95专业防护口罩，但没有防护服，因此张继先安排同事在网上订购了细帆布的白色工作服用作防护，并将这些工作服一直穿到2020年1月20日——钟南山明确新冠肺炎能够人传人。
In a report in the Changjiang Daily, Zhang followed up on reports of unspecified pneumonia on December 27 and 29, 2019. The hospital approved N95 professional face masks for her department but no protective clothing. Zhang arranged for his colleagues to order white canvas overalls online for protection until January 20, 2020, when Zhong Nan Shan was able to pass from person to person.
此后，医院给他们提供了三级防护服。
Since then, the hospital has provided them with tertiary protective clothing.
根据《中国新闻周刊》的报道，上报了不明肺炎情况的武汉市中心医院，则在1月2日起，要求医务人员之间不许公开谈及病情，不得通过文字、图片等可能留存证据的方式谈论病情，病情只能在交接班必要的时候口头提及。
According to the China News Weekly, Wuhan Central Hospital, which reported unknown pneumonia, was banned from speaking publicly about the disease among medical staff from January 2, and was not allowed to talk about the disease in words, pictures or other means that evidence might be kept, and the condition could only be mentioned orally when necessary during the handover.
艾芬在1月1日起只得要求自己科室的医护人员先戴起了N95口罩。
On January 1, Ifen had to ask his staff to wear the N95 mask first.
在1月2日同一天，中科院武汉病毒所的内部邮件显示，接到国家卫健委的电话通知，不得对外透露任何疫情信息。
On the same day, January 2, Wuhan Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences internal mail showed that the National Health Commission received a telephone notification, not to disclose any information about the epidemic situation.
据央视网报道，张继先所在的科室无一例医护人员感染，无患者交叉感染。
According to CCTV.com, Zhang Jixian did not have a single hospital staff infection, no cross-infection patients.
而在武汉市中心医院，根据《中国新闻周刊》的报道，截至1周多前，其医院职工达到新冠肺炎临床确诊标准的已达230多人，其中130人住院，100多人居家隔离，多位科主任与院领导“中招”。
At Wuhan Central Hospital, more than 230 hospital staff had reached the clinical confirmation criteria for the new crown pneumonia by more than a week ago, 130 of them were hospitalized, more than 100 were isolated at home and many of the directors and hospital directors had been "recruited," according to China News Weekly.
根据中国疾控中心2月17日发表的报告，截至2020年2月11日，在为新冠肺炎患者提供诊治服务的422家医疗机构中，共有3019名医务人员感染了新型冠状病毒，其中1716名确诊病例，而在确诊病例中，武汉就有1080例，占全国医务人员发病总数64.0%，死亡的5名医护人员均发生在武汉。
As of February 11, 2020, 3,019 out of 422 medical institutions providing treatment for patients with pneumonia had contracted the new coronavirus, including 1,716 confirmed cases, while Wuhan accounted for 1,080 of the total number of confirmed cases, accounting for 64.0 percent of all cases.
报告指出，可能存在非职业暴露造成的感染，但迄今为止，医务人员感染以及防护失败的具体原因仍有待深入调查。
The report notes that there may be infections due to non-occupational exposure, but to date, the specific causes of infection and failure of medical personnel have yet to be thoroughly investigated.
04几个问题围绕2019年12月31日前后，关于疫情，还有很多未解之谜。
04 Several questions revolve around December 31, 2019, and there are many unanswered questions about the epidemic.
据武汉市长周先旺的表述，国家卫健委在2019年12月30日接到报告后组织了专家组前往武汉。
According to Wuhan City Chang Zhou Shenwang, the National Health Commission received the report on December 30, 2019 organized a group of experts to Wuhan.
一个问题是，国家卫健委是先接到谁的报告后组织专家组的？是中国疾控中心主任高福的报告还是武汉市卫健委的报告？而中国疾控中心主任在意识到网络直报系统“失灵”后，从2019年12月31日到2020年1月20日，国家卫健委和中国疾控中心是如何了解武汉疫情的？是否有第一时间恢复网络直报系统？2020年1月31日，中国疾控中心副主任冯子健接受《新京报》采访时表示，在本次新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情中，“网络直报系统的启用没有那么早”。
On January 31, 2020, China's CDC and China CDC, aware of the "failure" of the network direct reporting system, said in an interview with the Beijing News on January 31, 2020, that "the launch of the network direct reporting system is not so early."
在回答关于何时知道医务人员感染的提问时，冯子健说，是19日钟南山到武汉后，当地、国家级专家把结果告诉了钟南山，直到钟南山20日晚上到北京后，接受媒体采访披露有医务人员感染，接着武汉市卫健委作了披露。
In response to a question about when he knew about the infection, Feng Zikian said that local and national experts told Zhong Nan Shan after the visit to Wuhan on the 19th.
如果此时冯才知道医务人员被感染，说明截止到1月20日，网络直报系统并未发挥作用，而中国疾控中心信息闭塞问题可谓十分严重。
If Feng didn't know that the medical staff had been infected, the network direct reporting system did not work as of January 20, and the information blackout at China's CDC could be very serious.
但是，在2020年2月17日发表的论文“新型冠状病毒肺炎流行病学特征分析”披露，2019年12月31日，全国各级CDC联合开始了新冠肺炎的调查，论文也是选取了“截至2020年2月11日传染病信息系统中报告的所有中国内地COVID-19病例”。
However, according to a paper published on February 17, 2020, "Epidemiological Characteristics Analysis of New Coronavirus Pneumonia," the paper, published on December 31, 2019, showed that CDCs at all levels across the country jointly conducted a survey of the new crown pneumonia. The paper also selected "all COVID-19 cases reported from mainland China as of February 11, 2020."
说明传染病信息系统似乎还是发挥了作用。
The Communicable Disease Information System still seems to be working.
值得注意的是，冯子健也是该文作者之一。
It is worth noting that Feng Zijian is one of the authors of this article.
根据中国疾控中心官网，中国疾控中心负责的传染病网络直报系统新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎动态监测功能在2020年1月24日上线，可实现新型肺炎的病例个案信息、诊治信息、感染来源等相关信息的快速报告。
According to the official website of the China CDC, the new-style coronavirus infection pneumonia surveillance system operated by the China Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) will have a dynamic pneumonia surveillance function on January 24, 2020.
这是否说明，在新冠肺炎疫情中，传染病网络直报系统在1月24日才发挥作用？这些问题，都需要更多的信息披露来回应公众的疑问。
Does this mean that the Communicable Disease Network Direct Reporting System did not come into operation until January 24 in the case of the New Crown Pneumonia epidemic?
2019年12月31日，武汉市将从2019年12月16日住院的疑似患者转移到金银潭医院进行隔离；世界卫生组织中国办事处接到报告，武汉出现不明原因肺炎；香港食物及卫生局开始部署防控措施，加强出入境口岸健康监察，并通知前线医护人员提高警觉。
On December 31, 2019, the city of Wuhan transferred suspected patients hospitalized on December 16, 2019 to Gold and Silver Pool Hospital for isolation; the World Health Organization (WHO) China office received reports of unidentified pneumonia in Wuhan; and the Hong Kong Food and Health Bureau (FHB) began to deploy preventive and control measures to strengthen health surveillance at entry and exit points and alert frontline medical staff.
而此时的武汉，采购年货的人流熙来攘往，百步亭社区的万家宴正在紧锣密鼓筹备，武汉市两会即将在5天后召开，半个月后开始的春运，数百万人流将从九省通衢的武汉流出。
Wuhan, meanwhile, is bustling with people buying New Year's goods, with hundreds of thousands of meals being prepared for the Ba Bu Ting community. The Wuhan Municipal Congress will be held in five days, and the start of the Spring Festival in half a month will see millions flow out of Wuhan, the thoroughfare of nine provinces.
“防疫工作是救火，看到苗头出现就要往上扑，不能说因为不能打救火铃，就不要扑上去，就当成没火情，怎么可以这样？你当做没火情，真有火的时候不就烧起来了吗？就是红布扑上去有什么不可以的呢？你不需要叫消防车，先把红布给扑掉啊，你现在把火苗当成了红布，你不就错了吗？” 一位资深人士评论说。
"The epidemic prevention work is to fight the fire, to see the emergence of the emergence of the need to pounce, can not be said because can not hit fire bell, do not rush, just as no fire? You do not need to call fire engines, red cloth to attack ah, you now flame as red cloth, you are wrong?" commented a senior person.
